urns removing stones from a pile, with *Alice going first*.\n\n- Alice starts by removing **exactly** 10 stones on her first turn.\n\n- For each subsequent turn, each player removes **exactly** 1 fewer** **stone** **than the previous opponent.\n\nThe player who cannot make a move loses the game.\n\nGiven a positive integer `n`, return `true` if Alice wins the game and `false` otherwise.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** n = 12\n\n**Output:** true\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Alice removes 10 stones on her first turn, leaving 2 stones for Bob.\n\n- Bob cannot remove 9 stones, so Alice wins.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** n = 1\n\n**Output:** false\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Alice cannot remove 10 stones, so Alice loses.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 50`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Math","Simulation"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Alice and Bob are playing a game where they take turns removing stones from a pile, with *Alice going first*.\n\n- Alice starts by removing **exactly** 10 stones on her first turn.\n\n- For each subsequent turn, each player removes **exactly** 1 fewer** **stone** **than the previous opponent.\n\nThe player who cannot make a move loses the game.\n\nGiven a positive integer `n`, return `true` if Alice wins the game and `false` otherwise.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** n = 12\n\n**Output:** true\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Alice removes 10 stones on her first turn, leaving 2 stones for Bob.\n\n- Bob cannot remove 9 stones, so Alice wins.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** n = 1\n\n**Output:** false\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Alice cannot remove 10 stones, so Alice loses.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 50`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/stone-removal-game/","problemName":"Stone Removal Game","problemNumber":3360,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","